P=\left\{A\in M_2(\mathbb{R})\mid A^TXA = X\right\}
(AB)^T X(AB) = B^TA^TXAB = B^T(A^TXA)B = B^TXB=X
(AB)\in P
\det(A^TXA)=\det(X) \implies \det(A^T)\det(X)\det(A)=\det(X)\implies \det(A^T)\det(A)=1
\det(A^T)=\det(A)
\det(A)\not=0
A
A^{-1}
A^{-1}\in P
A^TXA=X\implies X=(A^T)^{-1}XA^{-1}\implies X=(A^{-1})^TXA^{-1}
(AB)^T X AB = B^T A^T X AB = B^T X B = X
\det(X) \neq 0
\det(A^T X A) = \det(A^T) \det (X) \det(A) \neq 0
A
(A^{-1})^T = (A^T)^{-1}
A^{-1} \in P
